{"id":"340605787_Halogen_Bonding_in_Isostructural_CoII_Complexes_with_2-Halopyridines","abstract":"Three complexes [Co(2-XPy)2Cl2] (X = Cl, Br, and I) were prepared and characterized, representing a rare case of isostructurality within the Cl-Br-I row. The nature of halogen bonding (XB) in a solid state was studied by DFT calculations, revealing a tendency of XB energy growth for heavier halogens.","authors":["Sergey A Adonin","Mikhail A. Bondarenko","Alexander S. Novikov","Maxim N Sokolov"],"meta":["April 2020Crystals 10(4):289","DOI:10.3390/cryst10040289"],"references":["336009075_Halogen_Bond-Assisted_Self-Assembly_of_Gold_Nanoparticles_in_Solution_and_on_a_Planar_Surface","328544366_Halobismuthates_with_halopyridinium_cations_Appearance_or_non-appearance_of_unusual_colouring","339217030_Isomorphous_Series_of_PdII-Containing_Halogen_Bond_Donors_Exhibiting_ClBrI_Triple_Halogen_Isostructural_Exchange","338184253_AgL2Mo8O26n-_complexes_combined_experimental_and_theoretical_study","335848758_Halogen_Bonding_Beyond_Crystals_in_Materials_Science","332557300_Versatile_supramolecular_binding_modes_of_14-diiodotetrafluorobenzene_for_molecular_cocrystal_engineering","329662182_Metal-involving_Bifurcated_Halogen_Bonding_C-Bre2Cl-Pt","327470889_PtPd_and_IBr_Isostructural_Exchange_Provides_Formation_of_C-IPd_C-BrPt_and_C-BrPd_Metal-involving_Halogen_Bonding","327343229_Tetrachloromethane_as_halogen_bond_donor_toward_metal-bound_halides","326867341_Dramatically_Enhanced_Solubility_of_Halide-Containing_Organometallic_Species_in_Diiodomethane_The_Role_of_SolventComplex_Halogen_Bonding"]}